{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, by constraining models to replicate human thought processes, their performance is inherently capped by the human-provided exemplars, which prevents the exploration of superior, non-human-like reasoning pathways.",
    "To tackle these issues, we aim to explore the potential of LLMs for developing reasoning abilities through self-evolution in a RL framework, with minimal reliance on human labelling efforts.",
    "Specifically, we build on DeepSeek-V3 Base 8 and use Group Relative Policy Optimization (GRPO) 9 as our RL framework.",
    "The reward signal is only based on the correctness of final predictions against ground-truth answers, without imposing constraints on the reasoning process itself.",
    "Notably, we bypass the conventional supervised fine-tuning (SFT) phase before RL training."
  ]
}